      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_AgencyDashboard_AnnualEnergyUsageRetrieveCitywideCurrentVsPriorFY",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve and compare energy usage data for a city across the current and prior fiscal years. It calculates energy usage, demand usage, billed amounts, and BTU (British Thermal Units) for specified billing periods. The procedure uses a rolling 12-month period by default if no specific period is provided. It aggregates data from a published summary table and outputs it in a structured format for reporting purposes."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
